an class="n"&gt;emulate&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;an&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;environment&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;similar&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;production&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;easily&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="o"&gt;**&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Where&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;can&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;I&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;read&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;logs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;?**&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="n"&gt;An&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;automatic&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;tail&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;of&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;these&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;logs&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;is&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;started&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;when&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;execute&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;osqueryx&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;start&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="err"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;The&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;logs&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;are&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;prefixed&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="err"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;elasticsearch_log&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="err"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;foreman&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;output&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;If&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="err"&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;like&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;to&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;tail&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;these&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;logs&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;separately&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;you&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;can&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;so&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;by&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;invoking&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;docker&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;client&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;the&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nl"&gt;terminal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;$ docker logs -f osqueryx_elasticsearch_1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;**How can I restart it?**

Elasticsearch is run using Docker Compose. If you&amp;#39;d like to restart your running containers, you can run:
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;$ osqueryx restart&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;to issue a full restart of your containers. Keep in mind this will also restart ElastAlert.


**How do I know it&amp;#39;s running?**

You can `curl localhost:9200` to see if Elasticsearch is listening on port 9200 properly. You should see something like this:
